 and economic change, labour markets are undergoing major transformations. This book explores the changing fortunes of young people in Europe's flexible and precarious labour markets and the range of policies that are being developed to help them deal with the problems they face. The book draws on recent research carried out across Europe to highlight a number of key dilemmas for youth policy: what help is needed for young people and their parents in coping with lengthened transitions from school to work? What types of training and education are most effective? Is a switch from general to vocational education needed? Is workfare the right solution? The contributors, who are all leading authorities in the field, challenge the conventional wisdom in many of these areas. The book will be of interest to those researching and studying labour markets and youth policy, and to policy-makers and practitioners in these fields.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aYouthxEmploymentzEurope. 0aYouthxServices forzEurope. 0aYouthxSocial conditionszEurope. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Children's Studies.2bisacsh1 aBianchi, Francesca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBradley, Harriet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBradley, Harriet, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCarle, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCraig, Gary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDietrich, Hans, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFóti, Klára, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGautié, Jerome, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHammer, Torild, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relat